# Allowed UI Sources (Shadcn Only)

Use **only** components, blocks, or templates from these sources. Do not use other UI libraries or write custom components when a suitable, code-available option exists here.

## Single shadcn skill — read it for all shadcn work

The repo has **one canonical shadcn skill** at **`agent-os/skills/shadcn/SKILL.md`** (installed via `pnpm dlx skills add shadcn/ui`). **Read and follow it for all shadcn work** — both *how* to add/fix/style/compose components (CLI + Critical Rules) **and** *where* a block comes from (its **"Project rules — core-fe"** section folds in the selection workflow + the 20 allowed sources below). The former `shadcn-component-selection` skill is merged into it. Selection in short: on first build pick the single best source and implement; when the user wants options, present best 3 with links and ask.

- **CLI-first**: use the project runner — `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest <info|search|docs|view|add> …`. Check installed components (`pnpm dlx shadcn@latest info`) and search registries before writing custom markup. Add via `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <name|url>`; review and fix imports/icons afterward.
- **Project context** (from `shadcn info`): style `new-york`, base `radix`, icons `lucide`, Tailwind v4 (`src/index.css`), UI alias `@/shared/components/ui`.
- **Critical rules to enforce** (see the skill's `rules/`): semantic color tokens only (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground` — never raw `bg-blue-500` or manual `dark:` overrides); `flex … gap-*` instead of `space-x/y-*`; `size-*` for equal width/height; `cn()` for conditional classes; `data-icon` on icons inside `Button` (no icon sizing classes); full `Card`/`Tabs`/`Avatar`(+`AvatarFallback`) composition; use `Alert`/`Empty`/`Skeleton`/`Badge`/`Separator`/`sonner` instead of custom markup; no manual `z-index` on overlays.

